# Environment Variables Setup

Copy these into your `.env` file and fill in your actual values.

## Supabase Configuration

```
# From https://app.supabase.com → Settings → API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://qaxtzytoobsunlbofzzz.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6InFheHR6eXRvb2JzdW5sYm9menp6Iiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3Nzc0MTg2OTcsImV4cCI6MjA5Mjk5NDY5N30.hW8ZddNt70gQ3PYkrybGaR5FJ1p56G2252QzIida0Qw
```

**How to find these:**
1. Go to https://app.supabase.com
2. Select your project
3. Click **Settings** (left sidebar)
4. Click **API**
5. Copy `Project URL` and `anon public` key

## Firebase Configuration (SMS Authentication)

⭐ **NEW**: Using Firebase Auth for SMS instead of Twilio

```
# From https://console.firebase.google.com → Project Settings
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=YOUR_API_KEY_HERE
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=123456789
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:123456789:web:abc123def456
```

**How to set up:**
1. Follow instructions in `FIREBASE_SETUP.md`
2. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
3. Create a new project or select existing
4. Enable Phone authentication
5. Get credentials from Project Settings → Web App
6. Paste into `.env` file above

**Benefits:**
- ✅ Real SMS authentication (Firebase handles it)
- ✅ Built-in bot detection (reCAPTCHA)
- ✅ Simpler than Twilio
- ✅ Free tier includes SMS quota
- ✅ No backend code needed

## Development vs Production

### With Firebase (Recommended)
- **Dev**: Add test phone numbers in Firebase console (no actual SMS sent)
- **Prod**: Real SMS sent to any phone number

